Protocols and Ports for DevOps
Commonly Used Protocols and Their Port Numbers
In DevOps workflows, understanding protocols and ports is essential for configuring networks, securing systems, and troubleshooting connectivity issues.

# Network Protocols and Ports

## Application Layer Protocols

| Protocol | Description                         | Port |
|----------|-------------------------------------|------|
| **HTTP**  | Web traffic (**unencrypted**)      | 80   |
| **HTTPS** | Secure web traffic (**TLS/SSL**)   | 443  |
| **FTP**   | File transfer protocol            | 21   |
| **SFTP**  | Secure file transfer (over SSH)   | 22   |
| **SSH**   | Secure shell for remote access    | 22   |
| **DNS**   | Domain name resolution            | 53   |
| **SMTP**  | Sending emails                    | 25   |
| **IMAP**  | Retrieving emails                 | 143  |
| **POP3**  | Email retrieval (older)           | 110  |
| **RDP**   | Remote desktop                    | 3389 |

## Transport & Network Layer Protocols

| Protocol | Description                                      | Port |
|----------|--------------------------------------------------|------|
| **TCP**  | Connection-oriented communication              | N/A  |
| **UDP**  | Connectionless, faster but less reliable       | N/A  |
| **ICMP** | Used for network diagnostics (ping, traceroute) | N/A  
